The paper deals with active learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The focus is on halfspaces, which are a common type of linear classifier. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of non-linear kernels, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). The large-margin assumption is a key aspect of the paper, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
